---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Essential Tips for First-Time Car Renters | Tomobil Car Hire">
  <main class="min-h-screen py-16">
    <article class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-3xl">
      <header class="mb-8">
        <div class="text-gray-500 mb-2">April 15, 2025</div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Essential Tips for First-Time Car Renters</h1>
      </header>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>
          Renting a car for the first time can be both exciting and overwhelming. To help you navigate 
          this process smoothly, we've compiled a comprehensive guide of essential tips that every 
          first-time renter should know.
        </p>

        <h2>Required Documentation</h2>
        <p>
          Before you head to the rental counter, make sure you have:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>A valid driver's license</li>
          <li>A credit card in the renter's name</li>
          <li>Proof of insurance (if using personal insurance)</li>
          <li>Additional identification (passport or ID card)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Understanding Insurance Options</h2>
        <p>
          Insurance can be confusing, but it's crucial to understand your options:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Collision Damage Waiver (CDW)</li>
          <li>Liability Coverage</li>
          <li>Personal Accident Insurance</li>
          <li>Personal Effects Coverage</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Check with your personal auto insurance provider and credit card company, as you may already 
          have coverage for rental cars.
        </p>

        <h2>Inspecting the Vehicle</h2>
        <p>
          Before driving off, always:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Document any existing damage (take photos)</li>
          <li>Check tire pressure and spare tire</li>
          <li>Familiarize yourself with controls and features</li>
          <li>Verify fuel level</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Understanding the Rental Agreement</h2>
        <p>
          Pay attention to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Rental duration and return time</li>
          <li>Fuel policy</li>
          <li>Mileage limitations</li>
          <li>Additional driver fees</li>
          <li>Late return penalties</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Final Tips</h2>
        <p>
          To ensure a smooth rental experience:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Book in advance for better rates</li>
          <li>Compare prices across different companies</li>
          <li>Read reviews and choose a reputable company</li>
          <li>Keep all documentation until the rental is complete</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          Remember, a successful car rental experience comes down to being prepared and informed. 
          Don't hesitate to ask questions if anything is unclear, and always read the rental 
          agreement carefully before signing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
